Description: The Gnome desktop
DescDetail: <<
GNOME (GNU Network Object Model Environment) is a user-friendly
set of applications and desktop tools to be used in conjunction with a
window manager for the X Window System.  GNOME is similar in purpose and
scope to CDE and KDE, but GNOME is based completely on free
software.

GNOME Desktop provides the core icons and libraries for the gnome
desktop.
<<
DescPackaging: <<
	This should really be %n=gnome-desktop2.2-{shlibs,dev} but not gonna
	change it now.

	gtk-doc (lib devhelp) moved %N -> %N4-dev as of 2.22.3-1

	share/locale moved %N -> %N4-shlibs as of 2.22.3-1

	gnome-about (in %N) is now (2.22.3-1) pure python; keep
	dependency on %N4-shlibs for benefit of other packages that
	have Depends:%N and expect it to bring the .dylib and because
	%N shares same gettext dictionaries

	Remove stray silent dependency on popt. See:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=557022

	2.24 requires randr 1.2	so cannot upgrade for now. See:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=554263
<<
